## Command & Query Handlers — @nestjs/cqrs patterns

### Module setup — required once per feature module

```ts
import { CqrsModule } from '@nestjs/cqrs';

@Module({
  imports: [CqrsModule],   // ← registers CommandBus, QueryBus, EventBus
  providers: [
    CancelOrderHandler,
    GetOrderByIdHandler,
    OnOrderCancelledHandler,
  ],
})
export class OrderModule {}
```

---

## `commands/` — Command Handlers (write side)

A command is a **single user intent that changes state**. Each command has exactly one handler, auto-registered with `CommandBus` via `@CommandHandler`.

**Command object — plain data, no methods:**

```ts
// cancel-order.command.ts
export class CancelOrderCommand {
  constructor(
    readonly orderId: string,
    readonly cancelledBy: string,
  ) {}
}
```

**Handler — load → call domain method → persist → publishAll:**

```ts
// cancel-order.handler.ts
@CommandHandler(CancelOrderCommand)
@Injectable()
export class CancelOrderHandler implements ICommandHandler<CancelOrderCommand> {
  constructor(
    @Inject(IOrderRepository) private readonly orderRepository: IOrderRepository,
    private readonly eventBus: EventBus,
  ) {}

  async execute(command: CancelOrderCommand): Promise<void> {
    const order = await this.orderRepository.findById(command.orderId);
    if (!order) throw new OrderNotFoundError(command.orderId);

    order.cancel();   // ← invariant guard + events queued on aggregate

    await this.orderRepository.update(order.id, order);

    this.eventBus.publishAll(order.domainEvents);   // ← publish after successful write
    order.clearEvents();
  }
}
```

**Dispatching from a controller:**

```ts
// order.controller.ts
@Controller('orders')
export class OrderController {
  constructor(private readonly commandBus: CommandBus) {}

  @Delete(':id')
  cancel(@Param('id') id: string, @CurrentUser() user: User) {
    return this.commandBus.execute(new CancelOrderCommand(id, user.id));
  }
}
```

**Rules:**
- Always use `@CommandHandler(CommandClass)` — required for `CommandBus` routing.
- Always implement `ICommandHandler<TCommand, TResult>` from `@nestjs/cqrs`.
- Always call `eventBus.publishAll(aggregate.domainEvents)` **after** the repository write — never before.
- Always call `aggregate.clearEvents()` immediately after `publishAll`.
- `@Injectable()` — NestJS DI is allowed here.
- Inject via domain-layer tokens only (`@Inject(IXxxRepository)`).
- **No business logic** — the handler is a thin orchestrator. All rules live in the aggregate.
- Never throw raw `Error` or `HttpException` — throw `BusinessError` subclasses only.
- Never import Prisma types or call `prisma.*` directly.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — publishes before persisting (events reflect uncommitted state)
order.cancel();
this.eventBus.publishAll(order.domainEvents);
await this.orderRepository.update(order.id, order);

// ❌ BAD — missing clearEvents() (events re-fire if aggregate is saved again)
this.eventBus.publishAll(order.domainEvents);
// order.clearEvents() ← missing
```

