## `queries/` — Query Handlers (read side)

A query reads state and returns a DTO. It **never mutates** anything — no domain methods, no repository writes, no event dispatch.

**Query object:**

```ts
// get-order-by-id.query.ts
export class GetOrderByIdQuery {
  constructor(readonly orderId: string) {}
}
```

**Handler — `@QueryHandler` + `IQueryHandler`:**

```ts
// get-order-by-id.handler.ts
@QueryHandler(GetOrderByIdQuery)
@Injectable()
export class GetOrderByIdHandler implements IQueryHandler<GetOrderByIdQuery, OrderResponseDto> {
  constructor(
    @Inject(IOrderRepository)
    private readonly orderRepository: IOrderRepository,
  ) {}

  async execute(query: GetOrderByIdQuery): Promise<OrderResponseDto> {
    const order = await this.orderRepository.findById(query.orderId);
    if (!order) throw new OrderNotFoundError(query.orderId);
    return OrderResponseMapper.toDto(order);   // ← always return a DTO, never a raw aggregate
  }
}
```

**Dispatching from a controller:**

```ts
@Get(':id')
getById(@Param('id') id: string) {
  return this.queryBus.execute(new GetOrderByIdQuery(id));
}
```

**Rules:**
- Always use `@QueryHandler(QueryClass)` — required for `QueryBus` routing.
- Always implement `IQueryHandler<TQuery, TResult>` from `@nestjs/cqrs`.
- **Read-only** — no aggregate method calls, no repository writes, no event dispatch.
- Always return a **DTO**, never a raw domain aggregate.
- For complex read models (dashboards, reports), query handlers may use dedicated read-model repositories that bypass the domain layer entirely for performance.

